				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Stalkers in PoN<a name="54457"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 30 04 12:47 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Here's  a tip for the Stalkers camp:
<br />
First, I always charm kite here, seems to be fastest with least risk.
<br />
Charm the mob with the highest HP left, and tell it to attack the mob with 2nd highest HP left. each new pet should be highest HP of the ones in thje current swarm. This is easily done by cycling through the NPC targets (I have this hotkeyed to 'z').
<br />
If you do this, when you get to the last mob, you should have a pet and leftover mob at nearly the same HP. If not, charm the one with the LOWEST Hp, send it in on the higher hp mob, and throw a couple of DoT's on to even them up. Break charm, then you can kite down the last 2 very quickly, and don't have to mess with a nearly full HP mob to kite down at the end.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
