				<td colspan="2"><span>I can't believe noone has mentioned this yet...
<br />
The most likely scenario here is: &quot;You shoulda seen the one that got away!!!&quot;
<br />

<br />
It has been true for a long time that if you get a stalker that runs, and you don't stay on him, physically near him, he pops away to &quot;somewhere&quot;.  When his hitpoints start to return he starts making his way back, aggroing all the yard trash near him.  This creates some truly spectacular trains associated with stalkers (AND ITS THE KITER'S FAULT!!!).  Actually server lag might be to blame as well, they can lose track of you that way, but you need to KNOW when they do.  You just can't let these guys escape.  
<br />

<br />
When I did stalkers I always had snare in my lineup to stop the wanderers (usually when I was down to 2).  If one DID get away, I got my current group engaged with one another and camped/returned... Stalkers, for me,  were before Fading Memories ...sooo... Lose the aggro on the one that got away and life was peachy.
<br />

<br />
Before I realized this was what was happening I was bitching people out for training me... once I figured it out, people seemed to stop training me.. imagine that...
<br />

<br />
Reys / Stretto
