				<td colspan="2"><span>Just one quick question: Why run?
<br />

<br />
If you have your charm and chants loaded, why not welcome the adds?
<br />

<br />
Unless there are lag issues, I would gladly have them on board. The more the merrier. You should want to have a ton in your swarm, so much that you will want to cancel magic (my own preference) on your charm almost immediately after landing it and ordering per to attack. Then lay down 3-4 chants, toggle target, refresh selos, and hit charm again once mob one dies. 
<br />

<br />
It is far worse to have only two left from your swarm. Now that takes forever. 
<br />

<br />
As far as a bug is concerned, this would only bother me if something came out of the blue and stunned me (insta-death) and I didn't have deftdance available or kazumis. 
<br />

<br />
Other than that, I would love to have soft aggro from everything in PoN and own them. 
<br />

<br />
I was swarming there last night on Torv and did not notice anything out of the ordinary, but I will check again after the patch. 
<br />

