				<td colspan="2"><span>Wiladancer, i am presuming you are level 64 at least.  Likely 65.  Theres a big difference in the range of 52-63, and 64-65.  Banshee changes how you can cope with a train like this.  
<br />

<br />
If you have 12 possible pets and 24 others in your swarm.. then you are waiting on the respawn with 24 mobs chasing you a LOT of the time.  Sure you can chant them down one by one or two by two, but if you cant charm the majority of your kite, its gonna be a while.  Now with Call of the Banshee you can charm the yard trash and and deal with it, and fade when you want to dump em most likely, but you would get better xps over at hobgoblins and wraiths
<br />

<br />
Also mana regen can come into play for the typical bard that would swarm stalkers.  When I was there, I went from struggling to keep up with the mana drain when I killed em fast, to having no trouble, but starting to struggle with the rate mana drain from Banshee.  That was when I went on a FT binge.
<br />

<br />
BTW, I disagree that huge trains are best for swarming.  I'll sacrafice a few seconds of the charm-induced beatdown, for being able to break charm when they are lower hitpoints.  Whether I have 4 or 40 or 140 mobs, the slowest part of the kill is while I am chanting, I aim to minimize that time, not the charmed time.  If I can break every mob at 5%, a single round of chants and I can move on while he dies.  If 2 break at 3% and one breaks at 23% and I lose one, I am WAY behind where I woulda been had I had the control to break 4 charms at 5%
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
